JOHN TOWNSHEND, Respondent v. THE MAYOR, ETC., OF NEW YORK CITY, Appellants. Upon an appeal from an interlocutory judgment entered upon and in conformity with an order overruling a demurrer (the order not being appealed from) the judgment cannot be reversed.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Ingraham, J..

Decided January 5, 1891. • Appeal from an interlocutory judgment overruling a demurrer to the complaint. William H. Clark, counsel to corporation, and Woolsey Carmalt of counsel, for appellants. John Townshend, respondent, in person.

The Court (Ingraham, J., writing, Sedgwick, Ch. J., concurring) held as stated in the head-note.
